news.title: WeWork India slips in trading debut amid valuation, governance concerns
news.para: WeWork India Management shares debuted 3% lower, valuing the co-working provider at $950 million amid investor concerns over steep valuation and governance risks. The company, which licenses its brand from the bankrupt U.S. namesake, raised $338.16 million in its IPO.

news.title: Puravankara's pre-sales up 4% to ₹1,322 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Puravankara reported a four percent year-on-year growth in pre-sales to ₹1,322 crore in Q2 FY26, driven by sustenance sales. The company also saw an improvement in average price realization and customer collections. In the first half of FY26, Puravankara added significant developable area through acquisitions and strategic partnerships.

news.title: Kolte-Patil acquires 7.5-acre land parcel in Bhugaon, Pune
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers has acquired a 7.5-acre land parcel in Bhugaon, planning a project with an estimated 1.9 million sq ft saleable area and a ₹1,400 crore gross development value. This strategic acquisition aligns with the company's goal of delivering value-driven developments amidst growing demand. The NCLT, Mumbai also recently approved the amalgamation scheme between Kolte-Patil Developers and its subsidiary.

news.title: Builders face FIR after Delhi company accuses them of fraud
news.para: A Delhi firm claims it was defrauded of Rs 1.6 crore in a fake property deal. Representatives of Bhutani Infra and CBS International allegedly misrepresented property ownership. The firm paid an advance for a commercial unit at Alphathum's Noida World One. Accused executives are facing charges of cheating and criminal conspiracy.

news.title: HFCs get NHB support to diversify fund sources, loans may cost less
news.para: Housing finance companies in India will soon see lower borrowing costs. The National Housing Bank is offering partial credit enhancement on their bonds. This move aims to make home loans more affordable, especially for those seeking affordable housing. Eligible companies must meet certain asset size and credit rating criteria.

news.title: HC issues notice to Goa's town and country planning department on changes to building rules
news.para: The Bombay High Court has issued notices to Goa's Town and Country Planning Department regarding amendments to building regulations. These changes empower the government to approve relaxations for height and floor area ratio, a move challenged by the Goa Foundation and citizens.

news.title: Noida: Decade-old land row settled, Wave Mega City Centre to open up for real estate
news.para: Noida Authority has finalized a decade-long land dispute for Wave Mega City Centre, allowing the developer to retain 1.2 lakh sqm and surrender 5 lakh sqm. The reclaimed land will be used for commercial development, while Wave can complete viable project portions under revised terms after a settlement policy review.

news.title: Lucknow development body to open registrations for 500 plots in Anantnagar on Diwali
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) is reopening registrations for the Anantnagar Housing Scheme this Diwali, offering approximately 500 residential plots. The expansive project on Mohan Road, featuring modern infrastructure and an Education City, will maintain its land rate of ₹41,150 per square metre.

news.title: Releasing sewage into vacant plots? Checks soon at housing societies in Gurugram sectors 82 to 115
news.para: Haryana's principal advisor has ordered inspections of sewage treatment plants in residential societies across sectors 82-115 following complaints of untreated wastewater discharge. Strict action will be taken against violators. Additionally, civic bodies are intensifying anti-encroachment drives to reclaim public land.

news.title: Maharashtra government sets auction base price at 90% of sand available in block
news.para: Maharashtra has revised its sand auction base price to 90% of excavatable volume, reserving the remaining 10% for beneficiaries. This recalibration aims to align floor prices with saleable quantities and reduce pricing disputes. Annual e-auctions for river-bed blocks and e-tenders for creek-bed blocks are now in place, with a standardized one-year auction tenure.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders Ireo to pay 11% interest to NRI buyer for delay in plot handover
news.para: HRera has ordered Ireo Private Ltd to pay 10.8% annual delay interest to a UK-based allottee for an eight-year delay in plot possession. The developer also reduced the plot size while continuing to charge for the original area. Ireo has 90 days to comply with the order.

news.title: Noida: FIR ordered against Sikka directors for cheating homebuyer
news.para: A Noida court has ordered police to register a case against directors and employees of Sikka Pinnacle Super Structure Pvt Ltd for allegedly cheating a homebuyer of Rs 79 lakh. The company failed to hand over a booked flat and allegedly resold it, leading to charges of cheating and criminal breach of trust.

news.title: Punjab government forms special committee to create roadmap for real estate sector
news.para: Punjab's housing and urban development department has formed a sector-specific committee to create a tailored roadmap for the real estate sector. This initiative aims to foster structured engagement between industry stakeholders and the government, promoting a progressive and investment-friendly ecosystem.

news.title: Omaxe gets extension for township in Patiala after returning 60 acres to government
news.para: Patiala Development Authority has granted a three-year extension to Omaxe Limited for an integrated township project at Baran village. The developer will now resume development and maintenance responsibilities after returning 60 acres of land, resolving a 13-14 year old dispute and benefiting residents.

news.title: Signature Global to raise ₹875 crore next week via NCDs
news.para: Signature Global Ltd is set to raise Rs 875 crore next week through the issuance of non-convertible debentures (NCDs) on a private placement basis. The company's Debenture Committee has approved the terms for 87,500 NCDs with a face value of Rs 1 lakh each, carrying an 11% coupon rate. These NCDs will mature in January 2029.

news.title: Crisil inks 15-year lease for office in Mumbai’s Saki Vihar, to pay nearly ₹600 crore rent
news.para: Rating agency Crisil has secured over 2.5 lakh sq ft of office space in Mumbai's Saki Vihar for 15 years, with total rentals nearing Rs 600 crore. This move signifies workspace consolidation, while the vacated Powai office has been leased by Brookfield Properties to CoWrks India for managed office services.

news.title: Serious issues with IHFL's financial transactions: ED to Supreme Court
news.para: The ED has flagged serious financial irregularities at Indiabulls Housing Finance (now Sammaan Capital), while an NGO alleges the Ministry of Corporate Affairs condoned governance violations despite SEBI's adverse reports. The Supreme Court has summoned an MCA officer with original files to examine the ministry's leniency in corporate governance issues.

news.title: Construction and demolition sites, vehicular emission Trichy’s bane
news.para: Trichy secured ninth rank in the National Clean Air Programme, topping the state, but failed to break into the national top five.  Lack of regulation at construction sites, absence of recycling plants, and emissions from poorly maintained vehicles are hindering its progress.  Despite efforts, dust and debris from construction sites and uncleared silt on national highways contribute to air pollution.

news.title: DDA seeks technical help from IIT and DTU after basement flooding Dwarka apartments
news.para: Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has enlisted IIT Delhi and Delhi Technological University to investigate the sudden basement flooding and flooring damage at Triveni Apartments. Teams will inspect the site to determine the cause and recommend corrective measures for the recently constructed complex, which houses over 340 flats.

news.title: Saya Group to invest ₹550 crore to build residential project in Ghaziabad
news.para: Saya Group has partnered with Harmony Infra to launch 'The Horizon Residences,' a luxury housing project in Ghaziabad's Indirapuram. The joint venture will invest Rs 550 crore to construct 264 flats, with prices ranging from Rs 6 crore to Rs 8.5 crore.
